isOwner().details: Returns true if the caller is the current owner.

params._to: The address that will own the minted token

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to query the owner of

ownerOf(uint256).return: owner address currently marked as the owner of the given token ID

pause().details: called by the owner to pause, triggers stopped state

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Throws unless `msg.sender` is the current owner, an authorized operator, or the approved address for this NFT. Throws if `_from` is not the current owner. Throws if `_to` is the zero address. Throws if `_tokenId` is not a valid NFT. When transfer is complete, this function checks if `_to` is a smart contract (code size > 0). If so, it calls `onERC721Received` on `_to` and throws if the return value is not `bytes4(keccak256("onERC721Received(address,uint256,bytes)"))`.

params._data: Additional data with no specified format, sent in call to `_to`
params._from: The current owner of the NFT

params._approved: True if the operators is approved, false to revoke approval
params._to: Address to add to the set of authorized operators.

params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token being claimed by the msg.sender

tokenByIndex(uint256).details: Our Licenses are kept in an array and each new License-token is just the next element in the array. This method is required for ERC721Enumerable which may support more complicated storage schemes. However, in our case the _index is the tokenId
tokenByIndex(uint256).return: The token identifier for the `_index`th NFT

tokenOfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).details: Throws if `_index` >= `balanceOf(_owner)` or if `_owner` is the zero address, representing invalid NFTs.

params._owner: An address where we are interested in NFTs owned by them

tokenOfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).return: The token identifier for the `_index`th NFT assigned to `_owner`,

params._owner: address to query the tokens of

tokensOf(address).return: uint256[] representing the list of tokens owned by the passed address

totalSupply().return: uint256 representing the total amount of tokens

params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be transferred

params._from: The address that owns the token
params._to: The address that will take ownership of the token. Can be any address, including the caller
params._tokenId: The ID of the token to be transferred

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unpause().details: called by the owner to unpause, returns to normal state

approveAll(address).notice: Approves another address to claim for the ownership of any tokens owned by this account

balanceOf(address).notice: Gets the balance of the specified address

disapproveAll(address).notice: Removes approval for another address to claim for the ownership of any tokens owned by this account.

getApproved(uint256).notice: Gets the approved address to take ownership of a given token ID

isApprovedForAll(address,address).notice: Tells whether an operator is approved by a given owner

ownerOf(uint256).notice: Gets the owner of the specified token ID

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.notice: Transfers the ownership of an NFT from one address to another address

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).notice: Enable or disable approval for a third party ("operator") to manage all your assets

takeOwnership(uint256).notice: Claims the ownership of a given token ID

tokenOfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).notice: Enumerate NFTs assigned to an owner

tokensOf(address).notice: Gets the list of tokens owned by a given address

totalSupply().notice: Gets the total amount of tokens stored by the contract
